 from gsulliva enuxha eas asu edu glenn a sullivan subject re long distance ir detection summary results of ir beacon tracking hardware tests organization arizona state university lines one five sburton dres dnd ca stan burton writes i would like to be able to detect the angular position low accuracy of an ir emitting source at a distance of about one zero zero meters more is better in daylight the ir source could be emitting a signature i m leaning toward three zero khz square wave with five zero duty cycle i designed and built hardware in one nine eight eight that would output a logic level from a five six seven tone detector upon detecting a five zero zero microwatt led two eight feet away used a motorola mrd three six zero biased linearly in a dc feedback loop to servo out variations in sunlight and six zero hz from lights used no lenses allen sullivan